-The first Moscow multicultural school 1650 opens for first-graders on September 1, the Day of Knowledge

00:00:16.800 --> 00:00:18.900
-

00:00:18.900 --> 00:00:19.700
School 1560, are you ready to lineup?

00:00:19.700 --> 00:00:20.300
-

00:00:20.300 --> 00:00:22.300
Yeeees!

00:00:22.300 --> 00:00:26.300
Now we can see that you are ready. Dear friends, boys and girls, parents, colleagues, guests, let me congratulate you all on behalf of our school on the beginning of the new academic year.

00:00:34.400 --> 00:00:36.200
-

00:00:36.200 --> 00:00:40.200
From his very birth a human learns: learns to walk, to speak, begins to perceive the world, and so he learns all his life.

00:00:47.400 --> 00:00:49.500
-

00:00:49.500 --> 00:00:53.500
First, parents help him, than kindergarten and school offer their help.

00:00:54.900 --> 00:00:56.400
-

00:00:56.400 --> 00:01:00.400
We, school workers, really wish that our lessons will come in handy in your further life. 

00:01:05.900 --> 00:01:06.200
- 

00:01:06.200 --> 00:01:09.700
Lessons of love, good, fairness and mutual understanding.

00:01:09.700 --> 00:01:11.100
-

00:01:11.100 --> 00:01:15.100
We wish you success, patience and sun in your soul, let this year be the most successful. 

00:01:19.500 --> 00:01:20.500
-

00:01:20.500 --> 00:01:24.500
On the Solyanka street in September fresh will open once again my dear...

00:01:26.500 --> 00:01:26.900
-

00:01:26.900 --> 00:01:28.600
School!

00:01:28.600 --> 00:01:29.000
-

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:33.000
Well done! One more now: Here children of all the peoples in peace and harmony learn at the lesson that twice two makes...

00:01:38.800 --> 00:01:40.100
Four!

00:01:40.100 --> 00:01:40.800
-

00:01:40.800 --> 00:01:44.800
Good for you! Bravo! Who's hiding there tremblingly beneath a bunch of flowers?

00:01:47.500 --> 00:01:48.300
-

00:01:48.300 --> 00:01:52.300
 What will give us today the new generation? Who came here for the first time today?

00:01:55.700 --> 00:01:55.800
-

00:01:55.800 --> 00:01:57.900
Come on here, first-grader.

00:02:56.600 --> 00:02:59.400
Ofelia Frakelyan (the principal)

00:02:59.400 --> 00:03:01.500
-

00:03:01.500 --> 00:03:05.500
I want to congratulate first of all today's heroes, the first-graders, I want us to cheer them.

00:03:05.800 --> 00:03:07.200
-

00:03:07.200 --> 00:03:10.700
